title: Led Zeppelin - 1975.02.13 Uniondale, New York
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1975.02.13 Uniondale, New York   

Led Zeppelin
1975-02-13
Nassau Coliseum, Uniondale, New York, USA
Soundboard Recording
dadgad prod.
(Ron Wood of The Rolling Stones joining the band for Communication Breakdown on second guitar)

Recording: 
Excellent soundboard recording.

Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional board tape.

Tracklist:

Part 01:
01.Rock And Roll
02.Sick Again
03.Over The Hills And Far Away
04.In My Time Of Dying
05.The Song Remains The Same
06.The Rain Song
07.Kashmir

Part 02:
01.No Quarter
02.Trampled Underfoot
03.Moby Dick

Part 03:
01.Dazed And Confused
02.Stairway To Heaven

Part 04:
01.Whole Lotta Love
02.Black Dog
03.Communication Breakdown*

*f/Ron Wood on guitar

Comments: 
A great show! The band is strong, Robert's voice is in fair shape and Jimmy is blazing, especially on a great and very long version of Dazed And Confused and an epic Stairway To Heaven solo. Roll Over Beethoven is only a short vocal rehearsal but one of the encores features Ronnie Wood on second guitar, dueling with Page as they trade licks in an extended jam that sounds killer when Jonesy and Bonham jam behind it
